	 New Delhi, March 29: Japan has offered India a loan of over Rs 10,535 crore for infrastructure projects, including Calcuttas East-West Metro Project Phase II and the first phase of a dedicated freight corridor of the railways.          Japan is expected to allocate initially over Rs 1,140 crore for the East-West Metro project. The project will connect Sector V to Howrah, intersecting the existing Metro route in central Calcutta, and is projected to be complete in 2014. The total cost of the project is expected to be Rs 4,874 crore.          
	The agreement for the loan has been signed between finance ministry officials and the Japanese ambassador to India, Hideaki Domichi.          
	The committed amount will flow into the country in the next financial year and the year beyond.          
	The official development assistance from Japan will now touch Rs 155,840 crore, making India the highest recipient of such help from Tokyo.                  
	 Nashik (PTI): Malegaon blast accused Sadhvi Pragya Singh Thakur, who was admitted to Nashik Civil Hospital on Sunday evening, has refused to take food or medical treatment until the inspector-general of police (prison) of the Nashik Road Central Jail and a local court judge meet her personally, hospital sources said.                  
	 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): Six people, including three women, were killed and 40 injured when a truck collided with an Uttar Pradesh bus carrying pilgrims on the Delhi-Dehra Dun national highway on Monday. The injured have been rushed to hospital. Two of the deceased have been identified.                  
	 Rameswaram (PTI): A 12-year-old girl was killed by a thunderbolt as heavy rain lashed Tamil Nadu on Monday morning. As most of the thunderbolts landed on the sea, there was not much casualty, meteorological department officials said.                   
	 Dubai (PTI): Kuwait has decided to grant resident visas only to graduates from April to check the number of immigrant labourers.
                                                                                                                                              
